# Adapted from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/filter/
# (filter.n3 facts + filter-query.n3 rule, merged into one runnable document).
#
# Previously blocked on a missing string:lessThan builtin (see
# manifest.json's history) -- now implemented (queryengine.rs
# BuiltinKind::StringLessThan), so this case is vendored as a real,
# runnable fixture: collect every :param value lexically less than
# "Louie" into a list via log:collectAllIn + string:lessThan together,
# then decompose the collected list back into scalar per-member facts
# (list:in) so the result is comparable via this suite's simple textual
# fact-set check (a list-valued derived triple itself isn't, since each
# parse produces a fresh, non-comparable opaque list-term id).
@prefix : <http://example.org/#>.
@prefix string: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/string#>.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#>.
@prefix list: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/list#>.

:Let :param "Andy".
:Let :param "Bobby".
:Let :param "Louie".
:Let :param "Zoe".

{
    (?param { :Let :param ?param. ?param string:lessThan "Louie". } ?filteredParams) log:collectAllIn ?scope.
    ?item list:in ?filteredParams.
} => {
    :Let :hasFilteredParam ?item.
}.
